<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870619-0115 </DOCNO><HL> PPG Agrees to Build PlantWith Taiwanese Company</HL><DD> 06/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PPG FREST </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   PPG Industries Inc. said it agreed with Formosa Plastics Group to build a continuous strand glass-fiber manufacturing plant in Taiwan.    The venture between PPG and Nan Ya Plastics, a Formosa Plastics unit, is subject to approval by the Taiwanese government. PPG said the plant will initially have an annual production capacity of 20,000 metric tons. It will begin operation in early 1989.    PPG also makes the glass fiber in North Carolina and the Netherlands. Pittsburgh-based PPG makes glass, chemicals and coatings. Taiwan-based Formosa Plastics makes polyvinyl chloride, chemicals, fibers and electronics. </TEXT></DOC>